    "description": "\n    <div class=\"mountain-description prose prose-stone max-w-none\">\n        <p class=\"text-lg text-stone-700 leading-relaxed mb-6\">At 4,048 feet, South Crocker Mountain ranks among New Hampshire's celebrated 4000-Footers\u2014a \n        collection of 48 peaks that challenge and inspire hikers throughout the Northeast. This hard \n        summit offers a quintessential White Mountain experience.</p>\n\n        <h2 class=\"text-xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-8 mb-4\">Popular Routes</h2>\n        <p class=\"text-stone-600 leading-relaxed mb-4\">The most popular route, **Appalachian Trail**, covers 5.2 miles and is rated \n    Hard. AT approach to South Crocker.</p>\n\n        <h2 class=\"text-xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-8 mb-4\">Peak Bagging</h2>\n        <div class=\"bg-emerald-50 border border-emerald-100 p-4 rounded-xl\">\n            <p class=\"text-emerald-800\">**Extend Your Adventure:** Crocker Mountain lies just 0.7 \n        miles away, making it an excellent addition for ambitious hikers looking to bag multiple summits.</p>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    ",
